data.title: Breakfast Buffet
data.text:
This was my first time to their breakfast buffet.  It was average sized and had all the items you could want:  Omelet station, breakfast meats, cream chip beef, fruit, waffles, etc. but my favorite was the homemade crepes.  Delicious!
The table that housed the bakery goods had enormous donuts that were amazing!  One could make a meal just off that table.
My only disappointment was being charged for the beverages.  The coffee, orange juice and tea was not included.  I almost fell off my chair when they charged us for a glass of water.  That's unheard of!
But the staff was very nice and the food was good so we didn't say anything.

data.title: Long time Italian family staple
data.text: The DiThomasi family has run this iconic local eatery for many decades and they have a loyal following in the area. This was a long time stop on the way from the Jersey shore to Philly. First - the pizza is outstanding and the dough is made fresh daily on the premises. Good sauce and cheese and a reliably good pie. My personal fave here is the spinach ravioli - it's really large (you get four) and really good. The pasta dishes are very good and usually enough to require a take home box. The steak sandwiches are also good here as are the burgers. It's a family friendly place with pleasant service and a full bar. Mangia

data.title: Love it
data.text: This place makes me feel at home. Of course some of those dishes my mom makes so thats home. Family run. Always a pleasure.

data.title: dinner with friends
data.text: We went to the restaurant  for their  Sunday  land and sea buffet. It was excellent. The seafood selection was more than i thought. The carving station had prime rib, turkey, ham and also pork. Great selection for the price.

data.title: It was ok
data.text: The place needs a makeover inside. The area has had a beautify the outside so the passer by can stop and eat al fresco. However, it was a cold evening so we went inside, inside a time vortex that took me back to the 70's. The food was typical bar food and the prices were not 70's prices but something you'd pay for now in the second decade of this century. So it was ok if you want to go back in time.
